I make oranges with Fimo. Roll very small balls over sandpaper to create right texture, make small indent at the top and bake. I made lots and put them in a box woven from small strips of cereal box cardboard. I did the same for cabbages and cauliflower. This way you can make your own greengrocer. Miniatures Food, Food Miniatures Tutorials, Fimo Mini, Tiny Food, Clay Food, Polymer Clay, Doll Houses, Amazing Miniatures, High Schools">
                 <h4 class="pinCanonicalDescription">
                  Fimo...why?  Who cares.  It's so neat!!! I make oranges with Fimo. Roll very small balls over sandpaper to create right texture, make small indent at the top and bake. I made lots and put them in a box woven from small strips of cereal box cardboard. I did the same for cabbages and cauliflower. This way you can make your own greengrocer.
                 </h4>
